      </equation><para xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="import-auto-id2586235">3. Plug in the knowns, <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi fontstyle="italic">v</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{Δv} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi fontstyle="italic">t</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>, and solve for <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mover accent="true"><m:mi>a</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="true">-</m:mo></m:mover></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:semantics></m:math>.</para><equation xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="import-auto-id2412874"><m:math>
